# Testing Rules

## Test Framework

- **Playwright** for E2E testing
- Tests run in Chromium, Firefox, and Safari
- Global setup/teardown for authentication

## File Organization

```
e2e/
├── tests/                           # Test specifications
│   └── stack-details-app.spec.ts    # Feature tests
├── pages/                           # Page Object Models
│   ├── DashboardWidgetPage.ts       # Dashboard POM
│   ├── LoginPage.ts                 # Login POM
│   └── dashboard/
│       └── dashboard-page.elements.ts  # Element selectors
└── utils/
    └── helper.ts                    # API helpers, utilities
```

## Page Object Model Pattern

### Structure
```typescript
import { Page, expect, FrameLocator } from "@playwright/test";
import { elements } from "./dashboard/dashboard-page.elements";

export class DashboardWidgetPage {
  readonly page: Page;
  frame: FrameLocator | null = null;

  constructor(page: Page) {
    this.page = page;
  }

  // Navigation methods
  async navigateToDashboard(apiKey: string) { ... }

  // Action methods
  async clickRefreshButton() { ... }
  async clickStatCard(type: "content-types" | "entries" | "assets") { ... }

  // Getter methods
  async getStatCount(type: string): Promise<string | null> { ... }

  // Verification methods
  async verifyStatCardsVisible() { ... }
  async verifyTimestampFormat(): Promise<boolean> { ... }
}
```

### Frame Handling
For Contentstack iframe integration:

```typescript
async accessFrame(): Promise<FrameLocator> {
  const elementHandle = await this.page.waitForSelector(elements.appExtensionComponent);
  const frameHandle = await elementHandle.contentFrame();
  if (!frameHandle) {
    throw new Error("Could not access content frame");
  }
  this.frame = this.page.locator(elements.appExtensionFrame).contentFrame();
  return this.frame;
}

async ensureFrame(): Promise<FrameLocator> {
  if (!this.frame) {
    return await this.accessFrame();
  }
  return this.frame;
}
```

## Element Selectors

Centralize selectors in `.elements.ts` files:

```typescript
// e2e/pages/dashboard/dashboard-page.elements.ts
export const elements = {
  // Frame selectors
  appExtensionComponent: ".app-extension-component",
  appExtensionFrame: '[data-testid="app-extension-frame"]',
  stackDetailsWidget: '[data-testid="stack-details-widget"]',

  // Stat card selectors
  statCards: {
    contentTypes: '[data-testid="stat-card-content-types"]',
    entries: '[data-testid="stat-card-entries"]',
    assets: '[data-testid="stat-card-assets"]',
  },

  // Footer selectors
  footer: {
    container: '[data-testid="footer-container"]',
    refreshButton: '[data-testid="refresh-button"]',
  },

  // Helper functions for dynamic selectors
  getStatCard: (type: "content-types" | "entries" | "assets") => 
    `[data-testid="stat-card-${type}"]`,
} as const;
```

## data-testid Naming Conventions

Follow these patterns:

| Element Type | Pattern | Example |
|-------------|---------|---------|
| Container | `{feature}-widget` | `stack-details-widget` |
| Card | `stat-card-{type}` | `stat-card-content-types` |
| Count | `stat-count-{type}` | `stat-count-entries` |
| Label | `stat-label-{type}` | `stat-label-assets` |
| Button | `{action}-button` | `refresh-button` |
| Footer | `footer-{element}` | `footer-container` |
| Skeleton | `{element}-skeleton` | `stat-card-skeleton` |

## Test Structure

```typescript
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";
import { DashboardWidgetPage } from "../pages/DashboardWidgetPage";

test("Should display correct stat card data", async ({ page }) => {
  const dashboardWidgetPage = new DashboardWidgetPage(page);

  // Navigate
  await dashboardWidgetPage.navigateToDashboard(process.env.STACK_API_KEY || "");

  // Verify
  await dashboardWidgetPage.verifyStatCardsVisible();
  await dashboardWidgetPage.verifyStatCardData("content-types", "Content Types");
});
```

## Waiting Strategies

### Wait for data load
```typescript
async waitForDataLoad() {
  const frame = await this.ensureFrame();
  await expect(frame.getByText(elements.text.dataRefreshed))
    .toHaveText(elements.text.dataRefreshed, { timeout: 15000 });
}
```

### Wait for element visibility
```typescript
await expect(frame.locator(elements.footer.success))
  .toBeVisible({ timeout: 15000 });
```

### Wait for skeleton to appear/disappear
```typescript
async waitForSkeletonToAppear() {
  const frame = await this.ensureFrame();
  await expect(frame.locator(elements.skeleton.statCard).first())
    .toBeVisible({ timeout: 2000 });
}
```

## Popup/New Tab Handling

```typescript
async clickStatLabelAndVerifyPopup(type: string, expectedUrlFragment: string) {
  const frame = await this.ensureFrame();
  const pagePromise = this.page.waitForEvent("popup");
  await frame.locator(elements.getStatLabel(type)).click();
  const newPage = await pagePromise;
  expect(newPage.url()).toContain(expectedUrlFragment);
  await newPage.close();
}
```

## Error Handling in Tests

Use try-catch for race conditions:

```typescript
test("Should display loading state", async ({ page }) => {
  try {
    await dashboardWidgetPage.waitForSkeletonToAppear();
    await dashboardWidgetPage.verifySkeletonCount(3);
  } catch (error) {
    // Loading was too fast, verify final content instead
    console.log("Skeleton loaded too quickly");
  }
  await dashboardWidgetPage.waitForFooterSuccess();
});
```

## Global Setup/Teardown

### Global Setup (Authentication)
```typescript
// global-setup.ts
async function globalSetup(config: FullConfig) {
  const browser = await chromium.launch();
  const page = await browser.newPage();
  const loginPage = new LoginPage(page);
  await loginPage.visitLoginPage();
  await loginPage.performLogin(EMAIL, PASSWORD);
  await getAuthToken();
}
```

### Global Teardown (Cleanup)
```typescript
// global-teardown.ts
async function globalTeardown(config: FullConfig) {
  await fs.unlink("data.json", (err) => {
    if (err) throw err;
  });
}
```

## Test Configuration

Key settings in `playwright.config.ts`:

```typescript
const config: PlaywrightTestConfig = {
  testDir: "./e2e/tests",
  timeout: 30 * 10000,
  expect: { timeout: 5000 },
  use: {
    storageState: "storageState.json",
    viewport: { width: 1440, height: 720 },
    baseURL: process.env.ENV_URL,
  },
};
```

## Environment Variables for Tests

Required in `.env`:
- `ENV_URL` - Base URL for tests
- `STACK_API_KEY` - Stack API key
- `EMAIL` - Login email
- `PASSWORD` - Login password
- `ORG_ID` - Organization ID

## Running Tests

```bash
npm run test:chrome           # Run in Chrome
npm run test:firefox          # Run in Firefox
npm run test:chrome-headed    # Run in Chrome with UI
npm run show-report           # View HTML report
```

